status: MARC21-007: Configuration of playback channels of motion pictures

definition (en): More than one configuration of playback channels is available on a single motion picture.
scope note (en): An example would be a film with both monaural optical and stereophonic magnetic sound tracks.

definition (en): Configured to be played back on one channel.
Film is silent, has no sound or sound is on separate medium.
scope note (en): Also used when describing an item with separate sound.

definition (en): Configured to be played back or more than two channels.
scope note (en): Used for Dolby surround sound tracks and other multichannel techniques.

definition (en): Configured to be played back on two separate channels.
scope note (en): Use when the medium is not monaural and when it is not possible to ascertain that multiple playback sources are available or intended.

definition (en): Configuration of sound playback channels is not known.
Configuration of playback channels other than mixed, monaural, quadraphonic, multichannel, or surround, stereophonic.
